        <c02 level="item" id="d1e239">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>William Leete Stone Sr.</persname>to 
                  <persname>[George Lathrop]
                  Perkins</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1831 Aug 21</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>3 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Discusses Iroquois Indians, whose history
                  interested Stone; speculates on the spelling of the
                  Chieftain's name, On-kos or Uncas; says that, after
                  meeting the English colonists, the chief was
                  sometimes called Paquim or Paquiam, as well as Unca;
                  tries to get Perkins' help, as Perkins seems to be an
                  authority on the subject.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e261">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>William Leete Stone, Jr.</persname>to 
                  <persname>Benson John Lossing</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1877 Jan 16</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>1 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Asks him to become one of his subscribers; says
                  he is convinced that he will enjoy the
                  publication.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e283">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>William Leete Stone, Jr.</persname>to 
                  <persname>Benson John Lossing</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1877 Dec 4</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>Printed Postcard</genreform>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[In Stone's hand; asks him to remit $2.25, the
                  price of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Bargain</bibref>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e305">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>William Leete Stone, Jr.</persname>to 
                  <persname>Benson John Lossing</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1877 Dec 31</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Discusses the publication of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Bargain</bibref>and related financial
                  matters.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e330">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>William Leete Stone, Jr.</persname>to 
                  <persname>Joseph [Bradford]
                  Carr</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1885 Nov 23</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Requests volume XV of the 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Colonial History of New York</bibref>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e355">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>William Leete Stone, Jr.</persname>to 
                  <persname>H. Norris, Jr.</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1894 Mar 10</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>1 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Sends him the first installment [of autographs]
                  on loan.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e377">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>William Leete Stone, Jr.</persname>to 
                  <persname>H. Norris, Jr.</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1894 Mar 12</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Says he has sent off more autograph letters to
                  Norris with the promise of more to come; thanks him
                  for the subscription; advises him on the arrangement
                  of his autograph collection.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
